{"tid":1908003,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"澳洲政府：無證據持續社區傳播，一般大眾毋需停大型集會，可繼續握手","createTime":"2020-03-03T03:34:29.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-04T03:20:50.000Z","uid":302471,"like":11,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":17,"replies":[{"pid":"e3b8dbac1841a7092b0772fac40f8c9d027bf80b","tid":1908003,"uid":302471,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-03T03:34:29.000Z","msg":"Chief medical officer Brendan Murphy has played down the NSW Health Minister's suggestions that Australians should avoid handshaking. <span style=\"color: maroon;\">澳洲政府首席醫療官Brendan Murphy刻意淡化新南威爾士衛生部長提議澳州人避免握手</span><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nDr Murphy stressed that the two cases of transmission on Australian soil, which came to light yesterday, were &quot;very isolated&quot; and that there's no evidence of widespread community transmission here. <span style=\"color: maroon;\">最新兩宗澳洲本土個案為孤立事件，冇證據顥示澳洲有持續社區傳播</span><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nThere was no reason for people to stop going to mass gatherings or take any special precautions at this stage, unless they've come from countries where the disease is spreading, or they have symptoms of illness, he said. <span style=\"color: maroon;\">現階段冇理由要停止大型集會<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />，除非有人來自疫區或有病徵（講法似曾相識<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/photo.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />）</span><br />\n<br />\n&quot;If you have come back from South Korea or Italy or Iran, then we would certainly want you to practise some social distancing, not go to mass gatherings,&quot; he said. &quot;In that context, shaking hands, is probably best avoided. <span style=\"color: maroon;\">南韓、意大利、伊朗返嚟先要同社區保持距離，唔好集會，唔好握手（冇支那<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />）</span><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-03/coronavirus-updates-live/12019474\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2020-03-03%2Fcoronavirus-updates-live%2F12019474&d=HqwfJ7ndl2RLmQbQQ2LVpt8yddZnhMmQMHU13Um27G0%3D&h=26224bc6\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-03/coronavirus-updates-live/12019474</a><br />\n<br />\nThe Australian health minister, Greg Hunt, is talking about the low rates of infections for children. One of the very important reassurances for families is about on the evidence we have, limited transmissibility to children, which is very important for families and parents, and then the mild impact on those children on the evidence across the globe. Brendan Murphy adds to this: I thank the evidence around the world is that when children are infected, they are incredibly mild, in fact so mild that they almost don&rsquo;t have symptoms. <span style=\"color: maroon;\">澳洲衛生部長Greg Hunt非常安慰證據顥示支那肺炎對兒童僅為有限度傳播，Brendan Murphy話全世界兒童中招都只會好溫和，機乎冇病徵<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/chicken.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/mar/03/coronavirus-live-updates-china-latest-news-us-australia-deaths-markets-italy-iran-update-cases-italy-south-korea-japan\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2Flive%2F2020%2Fmar%2F03%2Fcoronavirus-live-updates-china-latest-news-us-australia-deaths-markets-italy-iran-update-cases-italy-south-korea-japan&d=HqwfJ7ndl2RLmQbQQ2LVpt8yddZnhMmQMHU13Um27G0%3D&h=c28164f6\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/mar/03/coronavirus-live-updates-china-latest-news-us-australia-deaths-markets-italy-iran-update-cases-italy-south-korea-japan</a>"},{"pid":"408d774e8911086813bada3af2077d145919ddbc","tid":1908003,"uid":290176,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-03